rooms.Name: On The Palace Steps
rooms.Description:
You stand before the Sultans Palace in awe of its majestic beauty.  Its
tall white towers have golden domes, and the sun makes it sparkle in all
its splendor.  Although the palace itself is not mammoth, it is by far one
of the most beautiful you have ever seen.  Certainly you would like to see
the inside of it and possibly even meet the Sultan and his beautiful daughter
Jasmine herself.  You check your hair and appearance just in case.

ExtraDescs.Description:
The doors stand around ten feet high, are at least a foot thick, and very
heavy. They are made of some sort of a hardwood, but what catches your eye
is the solid gold Sultans Coat of Arms on them.

rooms.Name: Solitary
rooms.Description:
You find yourself in a small, but comfortable room just off the royal chapel.
This a room is used for quiet meditation and prayer.  There are a few books
pertaining to gospel on the shelves, and a few parchments lying on the table.
You wonder if the Sultan comes here to pray for guidance in making his laws.

rooms.Name: The Royal Cloak Room
rooms.Description:
You are in a room filled with racks for hanging the outer garments of the
many guests of the palace.  This room is used mostly for the Sultans banquets
and balls.  It is large enough to store several hundred garments.

rooms.Name: The Front Foyer
rooms.Description:
You are in the front foyer of the Sultans Palace. Ahead of you the foyer
opens up into a large ballroom and banquet area.  To the West is the Royal
cloak room, Where you may want to store your coat before entering the 
Palace. The ceilings must be thirty feet high here, and everywhere you 
look up you see beautifully painted murals.  The palace is indeed fit for 
king.

rooms.Name: The Royal Guard Station
rooms.Description:
You have just entered a guard station.  The walls are covered with various
types of weapons and armor.  You can see a group of guards sitting at a table,
playing cards.  To the north lies a large banquet hall.  There is a stairway
to the east and a large foyer to the west.

rooms.Name: A Stairway
rooms.Description:
You are on a long stairway going to the second floor of the palace. 
Looking up, you wonder how the servants make the trip so many times a day.

rooms.Name: The Royal Chapel
rooms.Description:
You find yourself in the royal chapel.  There is a large altar against one
wall, and large windows of stained glass across the entire wall behind the
altar. Upon the walls amidst the sconces are very old oil paintings depicting
various religious scenes, and statues look at you kindly from the corners.

rooms.Name: The Royal Ball Room
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the southern part of the royal ballroom.  This room is
truly magnificent.  Hanging everywhere are brass chandeliers, and the walls
are dotted with ornate brass sconces on each side of every oil painting.
The floor is laid out in a breathtaking mosiac of marble.

rooms.Name: A Statue Of The Sultan
rooms.Description:
You stand before a lifesized statue of the Sultan.  The craftsmanship is
excellent and you marvel at the artistry in the facial features.  It seems
to be carved from a solid piece of pure white marble with tiny gold veins
running through it.  The artist certainly did the Sultan justice.

rooms.Name: The Royal Banquet Hall
rooms.Description:
A large banquet table that could seat an entire army fills the center of
this gigantic room.  Large vases are placed along the walls and corners, and
ornate paintings adorn the walls.  Here noblemen drink wine from golden
goblets and feast from tables laden with food.  Looking up you see there is
no ceiling here - you look straight up to the top of the beautiful golden
center dome, and the second floor balconies finished in a rich mahogany.

rooms.Name: The Hot Baths
rooms.Description:
This room has several sunken tubs in the middle of it, with vases of flowers
and incense burners stationed around them.  You see several pots full of oils
used for bathing, and many water vessels stacked against the wall.  You are
suddenly aching to sink your hot tired body into a nice hot bath.

rooms.Name: The Royal Throne Room
rooms.Description:
You stand in awe of a throne made of solid gold and fashioned in the likeness
of a massive elephant's head.  The tusks curve down to form the arms of the
throne, and the seats are plush blue velvet cushions.  Before the throne lies
a massive persian rug.  The Sultan sits here too engrossed in reading some sort
of a parchment to notice you.  His guards, however, are watching you intently.

ExtraDescs.Description:
The throne looks to be made of solid gold, and is formed into a massive
elephants head.  The magnificent tusks curve down to form the arms of the
throne, and care was taken to form their sharp ends into small golden globes
that the Sultan not pierce himself.  The seat and back of the throne are
cushioned with a rich blue velvet.  It looks very comfy - if only you didn't
feel so uncomfortable with that massive elephant over your head.

rooms.Name: The Royal Ball Room
rooms.Description:
You are in the center of the ball room.  You visualize yourself whirling
around with the partner of your dreams to the music, and let out a soft sigh.
What a life that would be.  You decide that you daydream too much and move on.

rooms.Name: The Crystal Chandelier
rooms.Description:
You walk into a room so dazzling you are almost blinded.  Millions of tiny
sparkles of light create an explosion of color as they bounce off your body
and dance across the floor.  Looking up, you see the source - a pure crystal
chandelier that must be twenty feet in diameter, with hundreds of tiny shards
of crystal hanging from it, that pick up every tiny ray of light and divide
it into many more in every color of the rainbow.

rooms.Name: The Royal Banquet Hall
rooms.Description:
You are in the center of the palace banquet hall.  The smell of something
delicious cooking wafts in from the north, and you are suddenly quite hungry.
The banquet table, empty now except for a few bowls of fresh fruit, will soon
be filling up with mouth-watering morsels.

rooms.Name: The Royal Pantry
rooms.Description:
Never have you seen a pantry such as this.  This room is so stuffed with
food you can barely walk around in it.  There are baskets of every fruit and
vegetable imaginable, plus things you have never seen before in your life.

rooms.Name: Jafar's Office
rooms.Description:
You are in Jafar's office in a deserted corner of the palace.  He has always
been unhappy about being tucked away here, but bides his time knowing that he
shall soon have the throne according to his evil plan.  The room is in a state
of disarray, and smells of dust and mildew.  You feel an evil presence here.

rooms.Name: Royal Ball Room
rooms.Description:
You are at the northern end of the ball room.  Your footsteps echo across 
the great expanse of dance floor as you cross the room, and you wonder how
many Kings and Queens, Princes and Princesses have danced on this very floor.

rooms.Name: A Sculpture of Jasmine
rooms.Description:
Here stands a a breathtaking sculpture of the beautiful Princess Jasmine.
So close is it to lifelike that you could almost swear it was the Princess
herself smiling down at you.  It stands on a small golden pedestal.

rooms.Name: The Royal Banquet Hall
rooms.Description:
You are in the northern part of the banquet hall.  The smell of food cooking
from the royal kitchen through the doors makes your mouth water and your
stomach rumble.  You resist the temptation to grab some fruit from the table.
It wouldn't do to spoil your appetite.

rooms.Name: The Royal Kitchen
rooms.Description:
This is where the sultans cooks prepare the royal meals, and during the
royal banquets, it is filled with up to 30 cooks.  In the center of the room
is one long table measuring 30 feet by 6 feet that is used for preparing the
feasts for the table.  You hope you will be invited to the next one.

rooms.Name: A Stairway
rooms.Description:
You are on a long stairway going up to the second floor of the palace.
Looking up, you wonder how the servants make the trip so many times a day.

rooms.Name: The Royal Music Room
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal music room.  It is from this large open room
that the beautiful music comes from when the sultan throws a royal ball.
There are many instruments lying on the floor and propped in corners here,
and chests containing some mandolins against the wall.

rooms.Name: The Rear Foyer
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the rear foyer of the palace.  Looking north, you see
the royal courtyard, in the center of which stands a large fountain.  To the
south you can see a sculpture of the Princess Jasmine.

rooms.Name: The Royal Library
rooms.Description:
You stand in awe inside a room that is filled to the ceiling with books,
parchments, and scrolls of every size and shape.  Some look to be very, very
old and fragile.  There are several gigantic piles of cushions lying around,
next to each pile of cushions sits a small table with an oil lamp.

rooms.Name: The Royal Sun Room
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal sun room.  Here you may play one of the many
games that noblemen play at their leisure, snuggle up in a pile of cushions
and read a book from the adjoining library, or just sit and gaze out one of
the many windows at the beautiful rose garden that borders the courtyard.

rooms.Name: A Stairway
rooms.Description:
You are on a long marble stairway that leads to the first and second floor
of the palace.  Looking up, you wonder how the servants make the trip so
many times a day.

rooms.Name: On The West Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire ball room.  The view from here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet above the first floor.

rooms.Name: On The West Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire ball room.  The view from here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet above the first floor.

rooms.Name: On The West Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire ball room.  The view from here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet above the first floor.

rooms.Name: A Curve In The Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a curve on the west balcony.  It seems to run a very long way to
the north, but around the curve to the east it ends abruptly at a closed door.
You wonder if you should even be up here, much less peeking in private rooms...

rooms.Name: The Sultans Bedroom
rooms.Description:
You find yourself in what could only be the Sultans Bedroom.  The massive
four-poster canopy bed is draped with dark purple silk curtains with gold
tassles - as are the pillows on the bed.  The floors are covered in thick,
plush rugs, and there is a magnificent portrait in a golden frame hanging on
the wall over the fireplace.  The view from the window gives a breathtaking
view of the entire city of Agrabah.

rooms.Name: The Sultans Dressing Room.
rooms.Description:
You are standing in a large room that has a large dressing screen, several
large mirrors, a few dressers and a large table against the wall with some
miscellaneous bottles and combs on it.  You assume that this is where the
Sultan dresses for his public addresses and such.

rooms.Name: A Stairway
rooms.Description:
You are on a long marble stairway that leads to the first and second floor
of the palace.  Looking up, you wonder how the servants make the trip so
many times a day.

rooms.Name: On The East Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire banquet hall.  The view from here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet above the first floor.

rooms.Name: On The East Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire banquet hall.  The view from up here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet about the first floor.

rooms.Name: On The East Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a long, open balcony that stretches all the way across the
entire banquet hall.  The view from here is staggering.  You can see almost
the entire palace from where you stand, thirty feet above the first floor.

rooms.Name: A Curve In The Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a curve on the east balcony.  It seems to run a very long way to
the south, but around the curve to the west it ends abruptly at a closed door.
You wonder if you should even be up here, much less peeking in private rooms...

rooms.Name: Jasmine's Bedroom
rooms.Description:
You find yourself in a room truly fit for a Princess.  There is a magnificent
canopy bed draped with silk curtains next to the window, and some of the most
beautiful persian rugs you have ever seen on the floors.  A small table sits
against one wall with various bottles of rare perfumes and a few pieces of
jewelry on it.  The window has a breathtaking view of the entire courtyard.

rooms.Name: Jasmine's Dressing Room
rooms.Description:
You are in a large room that has an ornate changing screen, a vanity with a
few assorted scarves and combs on it, a few dressers, and three large mirrors.
The furniture is sparse, but what is here looks to be priceless.  On the floor
is the largest, most colorful persian rug you have ever seen.  You assume that
this is the room in which the Princess Jasmine dresses.

rooms.Name: SPLAT on the Ball Room Floor
rooms.Description:
You have fallen over the railing to your death on the Ball Room floor.
Next time LOOK before you leap!

rooms.Name: SPLAT on the Banquet Hall Floor
rooms.Description:
You have fallen over the railing to your death on the Banquet Hall floor.
Next time LOOK before you leap!!

rooms.Name: The Sultans Closet
rooms.Description:
You find yourself in a VERY large walk-in closet - the size of a small house.
It is filled with racks of hung clothing, shelves full of shoes, scarves, and
cumberbuns. You wonder if the Sultan has even worn some of this stuff.

rooms.Name: Jasmine's Closet
rooms.Description:
You are in a walk-in closet the size of a small house.  Everywhere there are
racks of clothes hanging.  One whole wall consists entirely of shelves of
shoes and headwear belonging to the Princess Jasmine.

rooms.Name: The Steps To The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are walking down the marble steps into the Royal Courtyard.  As you
near the bottom of the steps, you hear songbirds singing, and a peaceful
feeling comes over you.  You hear the sound of water splashing to your north.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many of them in many sizes and colors.
The garden is immaculate and well cared-for.  The path curves here.

Exits.Description: You see a Guilded Cage amongst the roses.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal courtyard.  The air is perfumed with the light
fragrance of roses.  You hear songbirds singing, and it feels peaceful here.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal courtyard.  The air is perfumed with the light
fragrance of roses.  You hear songbirds singing, and it feels peaceful here.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal courtyard.  The air is perfumed with the light
fragrance of roses.  You hear songbirds singing, and it feels peaceful here.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many of many different sizes and colors.
The garden is immaculate and well cared-for.  The path curves here.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
Here in the midst of the rose garden stands a beautiful golden cage.  The
cage is full of snow-white doves, that coo softly as you approach.  Jasmine
has even trained them to eat out of your hand.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal courtyard.  The air is perfumed with the light
fragrance of roses.  You hear songbirds singing, and it feels peaceful here.

rooms.Name: The Tulip Fountain
rooms.Description:
You are standing in front of a gigantic fountain shaped like a tulip.  Its
top is a golden peacock, and the water from its tail fans out as if it were a
peacock tail, the sunlight turning it into a multi-colored light show.  The
Princess Jasmine spends hours here, feeding the goldfish and the songbirds,
and playing with Rajah.  You can plainly see why she loves it here.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the royal courtyard.  The air is perfumed with the light
fragrance of roses.  You hear songbirds singing, and it feels peaceful here.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many in many different sizes and colors.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many in many different sizes and colors.
The garden is immaculate and well cared-for.  The path curves east here.

Exits.Description: You see a Guilded Cage amongst the roses.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many in many different sizes and colors.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many in many different sizes and colors.

rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many of many different sizes and colors.

rooms.Name: The Rose Garden
rooms.Description:
You are on a path through the royal rose garden.  The sweet smell of roses
perfumes the air here, and there are many of many different sizes and colors.
The garden is immaculate and well cared-for.  The path curves here.

rooms.Name: A Musty Stairway
rooms.Description:
You are on a cold, dank and dark stairway.  You smell mold and dust, and
stifle a sneeze.  You hear scratchings around you and force yourself not to
think of what they might be.  You wonder if you REALLY want to be here.

rooms.Name: A Locked Room
rooms.Description:
So this is where the evil Jafar calls home.  How fitting - its disgusting
at best.  There are magickal items, scrolls, books, potions, and various
other items tossed everywhere.  In the corner you see a large bird cage of
some sort.  You wonder what kind of evil pet he keeps there.  The air is
moldy and rank in here and you find it difficult to breathe.  There is a
strange contraption with an hourglass in the center, and a large sphere of
some sort on top standing in the middle of the floor here.

rooms.Name: An Outside Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a large balcony in the great out-of-doors.  From here you have a
view of the entire courtyard and fountain, and the countryside beyond the
palace walls.  The sky is filled with stars out here at night, and Jasmine
sometimes sits out here with Rajah for hours just looking at them.

rooms.Name: An Outside Balcony
rooms.Description:
You are on a rather small balcony overlooking the front of the palace, and
there is a view of the entire city of Agrabah from this vantage point.  The
Sultan uses this balcony not only for relaxation, but also for making public
announcements to the people of Agrabah.  He hopes one day to announce that his
daughter Jasmine has chosen a suitor, from this balcony.

rooms.Name: Jafars Dungeon
rooms.Description:
You are in a dark, cold and dank dungeon.  You hear the skittering of tiny
feet, and the squeaking of something slightly bigger than a mouse.  There
are shackles on the wall, and various other items of containment and/or 
torture scattered about the room.  There is a tiny window up way too high for
you to see out of, with strong iron bars on it.
